				<div class="resTitle section">


























<h2>
	
    Creative Industries Bachelors of Arts Course Structure
    
	
</h2>


</div>

				

				
				<div class="resAccordion section">
























 


<div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12">
        <div class="panel-group accordion background-hidden" id="2a0a9db9-4696-4b2a-8a8b-d8f59229fb3b" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true">
			
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <div class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1571673150705-first-year" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#" href="#accordion-content-1571673150705-first-year" aria-controls="accordion-content-1571673150705-first-year" aria-expanded="false">
                            First Year
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1571673150705-first-year" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1571673150705-first-year">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1571673150705 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-opaque" id="4ab6e3ac-e1eb-48ee-aded-52a70b5611de" >

    <p>The program begins with a foundation year that will introduce you to the Creative Industries as an economic sector, as a subject of interdisciplinary study, and as creative fields that are being radically transformed by new technologies. You’ll begin your first creative-content module, selecting from a menu of more than a dozen modules specially designed for Creative Industries students. Your business specialization begins this year, with two core courses instructed by the Ted Rogers School of Management. You’ll also undertake coursework in communication, intellectual property, and creative urban design. Rounding out your 1st year will be two breadth electives that you will select from the humanities, social sciences and other disciplines offered at Ryerson.</p> 
<p>For details of the courses and tables, see the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/calendar/2019-2020/programs/fcad/creative_industries/">course calendar.&nbsp;</a></p>
    





</div>
